sses the highly topical issue of Nationalism and Toleration. Alasdair McIntyre concludes with an examination of Toleration and the Goodof Conflict. This book collectively offers an accessible and engaging commentary on the role of toleration in several areas of modern life and will be of interest to a wide range of readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aToleration. 4aPolitics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / General.2bisacsh1 aCarey, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzgerald, Garrett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIgnatieff, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacIntyre, Alasdair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendus, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuberger, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447097140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474470971423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474470971/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK